Installs ctx-* tooling binaries from an external CTX repo into this project's `target/debug/` directory so the Claude Code hook and other workflows can find them by their target path.

The script validates that the provided CTX_REPO path contains `crates/ctx-context/Cargo.toml` before proceeding. It builds all tooling packages from that repo via cargo with explicit `-p` flags (the PACKAGES list), then copies the resulting binaries into the local `target/debug/`. The BINARIES array differs from PACKAGES because ctx-cage's Cargo.toml produces two binaries (ctx-cage and ctx-run) from a single package.

Call with `scripts/install-tools.sh /path/to/CTX`, set `CTX_REPO=/path/to/CTX`, or rely on the default `../CTX` (CTX repo as a sibling). Re-run after copying template/ and whenever the tooling repo updates. This script handles binaries only; `scripts/update-template.sh` is responsible for syncing prompt files from the CTX repo to `./prompts` at runtime.